Fog crawled between garbage cans, thick enough to chew. The hustler pressed against brick, coin-flip poised between nimble fingers. "Maroni," came the whisper from nowhere. The name hung in the mist. Not a customer. Not a cop. Someone who knew his real game—and for whom he'd been waiting three cold hours to appear.

