Words failed him tonight, cursor blinking accusingly. Instead, he pressed his palm against cool glass, watching raindrops race each other down the pane. Each water trail—a story potential, a path chosen. Each drop—a character merging with others, gaining momentum. Somewhere in the storm was the person he'd written all his life without meeting. Not yet. But tonight felt pregnant with possibility.

