# Torn Hoodie | Chain-Link Fence | Screamed Name

Metal diamonds bit into his palms as he hauled himself up. Below, his name tore through night air—his government name, not his tag. Bad sign. The fence swayed under his weight, cheap rust sprinkling like cinnamon. His hoodie caught—a moment of panic—before fabric surrendered with a sick rip. He dropped to concrete on the other side, already running. Tomorrow he'd need a new jacket, but tonight he just needed distance.

